<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 625.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United
                                        States,</hi><hi rend="italic"> London,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-18"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 18, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> The proceedings at Liverpool under the
                            demand for the arrest of the pirates concerned in the case of the Joseph
                            L. Gerrity, and their delivery under the treaty, are very slow. The
                            magistrate has repeatedly postponed a decision for the purpose of giving
                            the parties time to show some authority for their acts of outrage. * * *
                            * * * * *</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>